'''9. What is the average number of extras (wide runs, 
bye runs, legbye runs, noball runs, penalty runs) 
conceded per inning by each bowling team? '''

df['total_extras'] = df['wide_runs'] + df['bye_runs'] + df['legbye_runs'] + df['noball_runs'] + df['penalty_runs']

inning_extras = df.groupby(['match_id', 'inning', 'bowling_team'])['total_extras'].sum().reset_index()

average_extras_per_inning = inning_extras.groupby('bowling_team')['total_extras'].mean().reset_index()

print(average_extras_per_inning)

plt.ylabel('Total Runs')
plt.title('Total Runs Scored vs Over Number')

# 16. how is the relationship between the number of runs scored and the number of extras conceded?

# Calculate the total extras for each delivery
df['total_extras'] = df['wide_runs'] + df['bye_runs'] + df['legbye_runs'] + df['noball_runs'] + df['penalty_runs']

# Group by match_id, inning, and over to sum the total runs and total extras for each over
over_data = df.groupby(['match_id', 'inning', 'over']).agg({
    'total_runs': 'sum',
    'total_extras': 'sum'
}).reset_index()

# Plot the relationship between total runs and total extras
plt.scatter(over_data['total_extras'], over_data['total_runs'],alpha=0.5)
plt.xlabel('Total Extras')
plt.ylabel('Total Runs')
plt.title('Relationship between Total Runs Scored and Total Extras Conceded')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# 17. Are there any notable trends in the distribution of runs scored by batting teams across innings?

import seaborn as sns
# Group by match_id and inning, then sum the total runs for each inning
inning_runs = df.groupby(['match_id', 'inning'])['total_runs'].sum().reset_index()

# Separate the data for the first and second innings
first_innings = inning_runs[inning_runs['inning'] == 1]
second_innings = inning_runs[inning_runs['inning'] == 2]

# Plot the distribution of runs scored in the first innings
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.histplot(first_innings['total_runs'], kde=True, color='blue', label='First Innings')
sns.histplot(second_innings['total_runs'], kde=True, color='red', label='Second Innings')
plt.xlabel('Total Runs')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('Distribution of Runs Scored in First and Second Innings')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# 18. Which batting team has the highest average runs per match?

# Group by match_id and batting_team, then sum the total runs for each match
team_runs_per_match = df.groupby(['match_id', 'batting_team'])['total_runs'].sum().reset_index()

avg_team_runs_per_team = team_runs_per_match.groupby('batting_team')['total_runs'].mean().reset_index()

highest_average_team = avg_team_runs_per_team.loc[avg_team_runs_per_team['total_runs'].idxmax()]

# 22. Which batting team has the highest number of centuries?

runs=df.groupby(['match_id','batsman'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index()

centuries=runs[runs['batsman_runs']>=100]

centuries_with_team= centuries.merge(df[['match_id','batsman','batting_team']].drop_duplicates(),on=['match_id','batsman'])

team_centuries = centuries_with_team.groupby('batting_team')['batsman'].count().reset_index()

team_centuries.sort_values(by='batsman',ascending=False).reset_index().head(1)
